  "prompt": "What are the major events that happened in 1997?",
  "response": "1997 was a significant year with several major events across various fields. Here are some of the most notable occurrences:\n\n### **Politics and International Relations**\n1. **Hong Kong Handover** (July 1):  \n   Hong Kong was transferred from British to Chinese sovereignty, marking the end of 156 years of British rule. The \"one country, two systems\" principle was implemented to govern Hong Kong\u2019s autonomy.\n\n2. **Tony Blair Becomes UK Prime Minister** (May 2):  \n   The Labour Party, led by Tony Blair, won a landslide victory in the UK general election, ending 18 years of Conservative Party rule.\n\n3. **NATO Expansion** (July 8):  \n   NATO invited the Czech Republic, Hungary, and Poland to join the alliance, marking the first expansion of NATO since the end of the Cold War.\n\n4. **Kofi Annan Reforms the UN**:  \n   Kofi Annan, the Secretary-General of the United Nations, proposed significant reforms to streamline the organization and improve its efficiency.\n\n---\n\n### **Science and Technology**\n1. **Dolly the Sheep** (February 22):  \n   Scientists at the Roslin Institute in Scotland announced the successful cloning of Dolly the sheep, the first mammal cloned from an adult somatic cell.\n\n2. **Mars Pathfinder** (July 4):  \n   NASA\u2019s Mars Pathfinder mission successfully landed on Mars, deploying the Sojourner rover, which transmitted valuable data about the Martian surface.\n\n3. **IBM\u2019s Deep Blue Defeats Garry Kasparov** (May 11):  \n   IBM\u2019s chess-playing computer, Deep Blue, defeated world chess champion Garry Kasparov in a six-game match, marking a milestone in artificial intelligence.\n\n---\n\n### **Disasters**\n1. **Asian Financial Crisis** (July):  \n   A financial crisis began in Thailand and spread across East Asia, leading to economic turmoil, currency devaluations, and widespread unemployment.\n\n2. **TWA Flight 800 Crash** (July 17):  \n   TWA Flight 800 exploded and crashed into the Atlantic Ocean off Long Island, New York, killing all 230 people on board. The cause of the explosion was later attributed to a fuel tank explosion.\n\n3. **Princess Diana\u2019s Death** (August 31):  \n   Diana, Princess of Wales, died in a car crash in Paris, causing global mourning and significant media attention.\n\n---\n\n### **Culture and Entertainment**\n1. **Harry Potter Series Launched** (June 26):  \n   J.K. Rowling\u2019s *Harry Potter and the Philosopher\u2019s Stone* (titled *Harry Potter and the Sorcerer\u2019s Stone* in the U.S.) was published, marking the beginning of the immensely popular Harry Potter series.\n\n2. **Titanic Film Release** (December 19):  \n   James Cameron\u2019s epic film *Titanic* premiered, becoming a massive box office success and winning 11 Academy Awards.\n\n3. **Notorious B.I.G.\u2019s Death** (March 9):  \n   Rapper Christopher Wallace, known as The Notorious B.I.G., was killed in a drive-by shooting in Los Angeles, leaving a major impact on the hip-hop community.\n\n---\n\n### **Sports**\n1. **Mike Tyson\u2019s Ear-Biting Incident** (June 28):  \n   During a heavyweight boxing match, Mike Tyson bit off a piece of Evander Holyfield\u2019s ear, leading to his disqualification and a temporary suspension from boxing.\n\n2. **Green Bay Packers Win Super Bowl XXXI** (January 26):  \n   The Green Bay Packers defeated the New England Patriots in Super Bowl XXXI, led by quarterback Brett Favre.\n\n---\n\nThese events and many more shaped the world in 1997, leaving lasting impacts on politics, culture, science, and society.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
